ball.http

Class ProtocolInvocationHandler

  • java.lang.Object
    • ball.http.ProtocolInvocationHandler
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DefaultInterfaceMethodInvocationHandler, InvocationHandler

    public class ProtocolInvocationHandler
extends Object
implements DefaultInterfaceMethodInvocationHandler
    Protocol InvocationHandler for ProtocolClient. The invoke(Object,Method,Object[]) translates the interface Method invocation into an HttpMessage through a ProtocolRequestBuilder. If the Method.getReturnType() is assignable from the generated HttpMessage, then it is simply returned; otherwise, the request is executed through ProtocolClient.client() with the ProtocolClient.context(). If the Method.getReturnType() is HttpResponse then the response is returned with no further processing (and the caller is responsible for consuming any entities). Otherwise, a ProtocolResponseHandler is provided to the call.
    Version:
    $Revision: 7215 $
    Author:
    Allen D. Ball
